@Node About "About WWSpellCon"

                               About WWSpellCon
                               ----------------

@{i}WWSpellCon@{ui} is an AmigaDOS script which will convert a Wordworth AGA
dictionary disk to a format which can be used with Wordworth 1.0.

I wrote this script after my brother's Wordworth 1.0 dictionary disk became
corrupted, and there wasn't a backup to hand. However, after a bit of
fiddling, I got my Wordworth AGA dictionary disk to work with his system,
and decided to write this script to make the task a bit easier in the
future.

From feedback I have received, it seems that all versions of Wordworth AGA
(Including Version 4) use the same dictionary format. As a consequence,
this converter should work correctly with all of them.

This script has been tested successfully with the following conversion:

  Wordworth 1200/4000 Special Edition ---> Wordworth v1.0

I would much appreciate it if you e-mailed me with the details of any other
configurations that you use this script on.

@EndNode

@Node Requirements "Requirements"

                               Requirements
                               ------------

@{i}WWSpellCon@{ui} is a standard AmigaDOS script. It should run on any Amiga system
with no problems.

The script does use a few commands from your C: directory though. For ease
of use you should either have two floppy drives, or have booted from a hard
disk. This will avoid frantic disk swapping!

Test system:

Amiga A1200, 2 Megabytes Chip RAM, 540Mb IDE hard drive.

@EndNode

@Node Usage "Usage"

                                   Usage
                                   -----

             @{b}WARNING!! Use a *backup* of your dictionary disk!@{ub}

Loading
-------

@{i}WWSpellCon@{ui} can be run from either the CLI or Workbench.

FROM THE CLI:        Type @{b}WWSpellCon@{ub} and press [RETURN]
FROM THE WORKBENCH:  Double click on the icon.

Note: You may get the following error message when attempting to run
@{i}WWSpellCon@{ui} from the CLI:

   "WWSpellCon: file is not executable"

This occurs if the "script" protection bit wasn't set properly when the
script was unarchived. To solve the problem simply type:

   protect WWSpellCon +s

Once Running
------------

@{i}WWSpellCon@{ui} will announce itself and then give the warning:

   "Warning! Please use a backup of your dictionary disk!"

HEED THIS WARNING! I have tested @{i}WWSpellCon@{ui}  to the best of my ability.
However, there is always the chance that something weird will happen, and
your disk will be corrupted. So, only use a @{b}backup@{ub} of your dictionary
disk.

When prompted, hit Y and [RETURN] to continue, or N and [RETURN] to exit.

Then you will be asked:

   "Please insert your Wordworth AGA Dictionary Disk into a floppy drive."
   "Then press [RETURN]"

Do as prompted. The conversion will then take place, and after a few disk
whirrs you will be told:

   "Conversion Completed!"
   "The disk is now a Wordworth 1.0 dictionary disk."

It's done!
@EndNode

